OL,6,FColder temperatures can be difficult
OL,7,Ffor a person with dementia to adjust
OL,8,Fto, and they may not always be able to
OL,9,Fcommunicate that they are cold ` or
OL,10,Fthey may not even recognise it
OL,11,Fthemselves," the charity said.
OL,13,FIt advised the public to check in on
OL,14,Floved ones, friends and neighbours
OL,15,Fliving with the condition.
